{"key":"post-9344768","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9344768</id>\n<content>Simply get a bottle of red wine and drink all but 1&quot; in the bottom.&amp;nbsp; Set the bottle in your fruiting chamber and the gnats will enter the wine bottle and drown.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Contrary to the other posters, I've never seen gnats do much damage.&amp;nbsp; They don't eat much, and they won't breed in your bulks substrates unless you made them too wet for mycelium to grow anyway.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Normally, they come from the soil of your houseplants, but if your terrarium has any standing water, that might be what brought them.&amp;nbsp; Other species tend to breed in the bathtub drain, and you can kill those with Drano.&amp;nbsp; Put a rag over the drain after you pour the drano in to hold the fumes, which kill the gnats.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Search for gnatrol.&amp;nbsp; It's a BT for fungus gnats.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9345271</next>\n<prev>9343482</prev>\n<first>9343423</first>\n<last>9346550</last>\n<when>1228169245</when>\n<utime>12/02/08 12:07 AM</utime>\n</post>"}